The paper discusses the interaction between humans and machine learning algorithms, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also touches upon the biases that can arise in this interaction, which is relevant to the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms in recommender systems and information filters, which falls under the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper proposes a theoretical model for iterated learning, which is relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
